<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Changes made in reference to <a href="http://framework.zend.com/issues/browse/ZF-1568">http://framework.zend.com/issues/browse/ZF-1568</a> alter the expected functionality of Zend_View_Helper_FormCheckbox and break backwards compatibility.</p>

<p>Documented functionality states that the first option in $options is the default checked value.  However, if $value is set and the checkbox should not checked by default ($value != $option[0]), two form fields (1 hidden, 1 checkbox) are returned with the value of $value, making it impossible to get the default checked value ($option[0]) returned from the form.</p>

